summary: Hi. Michael Sheen has clearly taken over DT's blogs on tumblr. It's pretty much all about him, now. And not many new arrivals...
question: Hi. Michael Sheen has clearly taken over DT's blogs on tumblr. It's pretty much all about him, now. And not many new arrivals from Sheenland to DT territories. I like Michael a lot but not quite sure I'm ready for this. What do you think? Am I wrong?
answer:
I hope I’m reading this correctly. It seems to me like you’re saying that you’re worried about Michael taking over here on Tumblr while David gets pushed to the side?

I don’t think Michael could ever take David’s place as Tumblr royalty, if that’s what you’re worried about. Certainly, he may join David as one of Tumblr’s favorite men, and I really hope he does. They’re both great. And Michael is certainly getting a lot more attention now than he did before, and I love that. He’s a very talented actor and a wonderful person and he deserves to finally get some recognition after all his years of hard work.

I’m kind of worried about the opposite happening, though: I’m worried he’ll get this sudden burst of Tumblr fame and then fall to the wayside again, or that someone will find something Problematic™ about him and ruin him for the rest of us.

I’ll admit, as a fan of David Tennant and someone who was on Tumblr at the height of his popularity here, it is a bit strange to see so much of Michael Sheen in spaces that used to be nothing but David Tennant, but I also think it’s nice. They compliment each other well and I don’t think it’s a bad thing. It isn’t anything to be worried about, really. There will always be a place for David on Tumblr, but now there is a place for Michael as well.

tags: kilgrave is marvel's best villain don't @ me
summary: I hate 1.09 of Jessica Jones (Sin Bin) because we see Kilgrave vulnerable. He's disheveled, he's crying, and he's laying curled...
body:
I hate 1.09 of Jessica Jones (Sin Bin) because we see Kilgrave vulnerable. He’s disheveled, he’s crying, and he’s laying curled up on the floor with his hands over his ears like a scared child.

Don’t get me wrong, his usual demeanor gives me the full-body shiver and an immense internal feeling of nails on a chalkboard. But when he’s dressed to the nines in his suites, perfect hair, flashing smile, and dead eyes, he looks like the monster he is.

But vulnerable Kilgrave feels like a human, and I hate that. Disgust and sympathy go as well together as milk and orange juice, and both give me a similar sensation in the stomach.

When he shows up later in Jessica’s apartment after stitching his wounds, he’s easier to deal with. Because I’m terrified, as I usually am of him. But he looks terrifying, not like the traumatised 10-year-old he appears to be in the sin bin. It makes my fear feel irrational seeing him like that. It’s much easier to be afraid when I don’t have to face the rest of who he is; broken.

summary: i just have talked with my mom about how good actor Michael Sheen is and she asked me how he looks like so I showed her this...
body:
i just have talked with my mom about how good actor Michael Sheen is and she asked me how he looks like so I showed her this photo, because it was the first I could find on my phone

and the first thing my mom said after she saw this picture was ‘oh, this boys are so gay and in love with each other… so one with the ice cream is Michael Sheen, right?’

She never seen the Good Omens. She never read the book. She didn’t even know who is Michael Sheen and David Tennant.

And she said that these two were in love, when she saw one (1) picture of them.

I’m screaming.

(p.s. sorry for my grammar, i don’t know english very good)
